Police said three juveniles and two adults were inside the vehicle.

The driver, a 17-year-old from Saco, was charged with violation of juvenile probation, reckless conduct with a dangerous weapon and eluding police, each charge a felony.

That teen was taken to Long Creek Youth Youth Development Center in South Portland, police said.

Jazya Swan, 18, of South Portland, was charged with unauthorized use of a vehicle, violating conditions of release and receiving stolen property. He was being held on $750 bail Friday at the Androscoggin County Jail in Auburn.

A 15-year-old girl was charged with unauthorized use of a vehicle and later released to her family. Two other teens, 17 and 18, were charged with liquor violations.

The vehicle the teens had been riding in, a 2024 Ford Maverick, had been reported stolen from a home in Saco earlier in the morning. Saco police had attempted to stop the vehicle, but the driver sped away.

Androscoggin County Sheriff’s officials said more charges are likely as they work with Portland police to investigate a string of vehicle burglaries in that city.

